%h2 Usage

%h4 Rails >= 3.0.4
%pre
  rails new &lt;application-name&gt; --skip-test-unit --skip-prototype --template=https://github.com/sampierson/rails-templates/raw/master/itdoesnothing.rb

%h4 Rails 3.0 to 3.0.3
There is a bug in Rails versions < 3.0.4 that will not allow you to use https addresses for templates.
So just checkout the template repository and run the template locally:
%pre
  git clone git://github.com/sampierson/rails-templates.git
  export TEMPLATES_REPOSITORY=`pwd`/rails-templates
  rails new &lt;application-name&gt; --skip-test-unit --skip-prototype --template=rails-templates/itdoesnothing.rb

